    "Body": " Location: San Francisco, CA Coinbase has built the world's leading compliant cryptocurrency platform serving over 30 million accounts in more than 100 countries. With multiple successful products, and our vocal advocacy for blockchain technology, we have played a major part in mainstream awareness and adoption of cryptocurrency. We are proud to offer an entire suite of products that are helping build the cryptoeconomy, and increase economic freedom around the world. There are a few things we look for across all hires we make at Coinbase, regardless of role or team. First, we assess whether a candidate demonstrates our values: Clear Communication, Positive Energy, Efficient Execution, and Continuous Learning. Second, we look for signals that a candidate will thrive in a culture like ours, where we default to trust, embrace feedback, disrupt ourselves, and expect sustained high performance because we play as a championship team. Finally, we seek people with the desire and capacity to build and share expertise in the frontier technologies of crypto and blockchain, in whatever way is most relevant to their role. Read more about our values and culture here. We\u2019re looking for a seasoned Marketing and UX Writing leader with expertise designing, building, and scaling content systems at a fast-growing, category-defining company. You will lead efforts to apply a consistent Coinbase voice inside our products, brand content, and support content, creating guidelines others can draw from, and systems for reviews that leverage the right stakeholders across Product, Design, and Brand. Coinbase is the leader of an entirely new industry and every choice we make with our words must be intentional, considered, and consistent\u2014that\u2019s how we maintain the hard-won trust we\u2019ve earned over the course of our 8 years. This person should be equally comfortable drafting clear and impactful copy, as they are in articulating the \u201cwhy\u201d behind the words\u2014workshopping, refining, and defending frameworks they\u2019ve created to make decisions. The ideal candidate will have the right combination of vision, ambition, judgement, editorial chops, flexibility, creative ideas, and strategic thinking. We\u2019re looking for someone with a keen ability to prioritize, separate internal signal from noise, and quickly and efficiently determine where and how to focus efforts for maximum impact. This role reports in to the Director of Editorial and Creative Services and will work closely with the Product Design Lead to align on prioritization across Coinbase product needs. What You\u2019ll Be Doing (ie. Job Duties) Write and edit for the Coinbase voice across a wide range of brand and product efforts, from landing pages to social media posts. Be the world\u2019s most meticulous words geek to ensure all content is relatable, accurate, and actionable. Direct and protect the brand voice in all work. Own the master \u201cstyle guide\u201d for all words ensuring consistency of tone and glossary of terms across all brand touch points. Manage and direct external writing vendors for Coinbase Earn video production. Build and own product content systems, collaborating with cross-functional product and design leaders to drive reviews and alignment around content frameworks. Lead the editorial calendar process across products and channels, including blog, events, social, etc. Work highly collaboratively with the Growth, Pro, and additional product teams to support the company\u2019s product launches and goals through content and social media efforts. What We Look For In You (ie. Job Requirements) Experience managing cross-functional initiatives involving multiple stakeholders across the organization. A hands\u2019 on approach as a \u201cbuilder.\u201d In shades of gray, you are comfortable devising an informed point of view. You don\u2019t need firm guidelines in place in order to get started. In fact, you are happy to put something down that everyone can work from. A demonstrated ability to understand complex subject matter such as financial instruments and market dynamics, along with the skills needed to simplify and explain these topics for a broad audience of stakeholders. Systems thinking. Demonstrable skill and knack for articulating the \u201cwhy\u201d and \u201chow,\u201d not just the \u201cwhat.\u201d An understanding of how to scale writing by creating guidelines and \u201csource code.\u201d Analytical rigor; a high bar for integrity, trust and quality; and a guiding curiosity to stay on the cutting edge of this fast-moving world. A strategic mindset. You should bring creative solutions to every problem and never see a challenge as insurmountable. A passion for crypto and the economic freedom it can offer. Our mission is to create an open financial system for the world\u2014we want you to help. Curiosity and an open mind. We\u2019re a culture of learners and we welcome a humble approach. Allergy to jargon and relentless push for accuracy. We care about what we say and how we say it. Every word matters. Nice To Haves Experience in FinTech, crypto or traditional financial services. 8-10 years relevant work experience in house at a technology company. Coinbase is committed to diversity in its workforce and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and to review all of our job postings to minimize biased language. Coinbase does not make hiring or employment decisions on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, gender, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy, sex, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, citizenship, or any other basis protected by applicable local, state or federal law. Coinbase will also consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records in a manner consistent with San Francisco\u2019s Fair Chance Ordinance and similar local laws. Global Data Privacy Notice for Job Candidates and Applicants Depending on your location, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) may regulate the way we manage the data of job applicants. Our full notice outlining how your data will be processed as part of the application procedure for application locations is available here: Ireland/EU, United Kingdom, and California. By submitting your application, you are agreeing to our use and processing of your data as required. ", 
